20/10/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Police arrested a dozen members of the border police in the region of Gjilan/Gnjilane, for suspected abuse of office and bribery Monday (October 19th).
Police Director Sheremet Ahmeti said all 12 were immediately suspended, pending further investigation.
He added that they are members of different ethnicities and have been acting as a group.
The investigation began two months ago.
(TV21, Top News, Kohavision - 19/10/09)
